## 2. Testing the Compiler

Let's feed some valid EME-GIR source code into our new compiler engine.

```python
eme_gir_source = """
// A tablet recording an offering
{d}god =ba "Enlil";
{ninda} barley_shekels =ba 125.5;
{im} temple_record =ba "Offering successful";

barley_shekels.ibĝare;
temple_record.ibĝare;
"""

# Compile to target language (Python)
compiled_python_code = compiler.compile(eme_gir_source)

print("--- EMITTED PYTHON CODE ---")
print(compiled_python_code)
print("\n--- RUNNING EXECUTABLE ---")
exec(compiled_python_code)

```

### Expected Output:

```text
--- EMITTED PYTHON CODE ---
# --- Compiled from EME-GIR (CuneiScript) ---
god = "Enlil"
barley_shekels = 125.5
temple_record = "Offering successful"
print(barley_shekels)
print(temple_record)

--- RUNNING EXECUTABLE ---
125.5
Offering successful

```

